[Canine distemper virus is probably the pathogen that has the greatest impact on wild carnivore populations at the domestic-wildlife interface. It is very important to make sure to keep the vaccination schemes of all dogs in the area up to date.

For a video of a raccoon with distemper go to
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H22KFjDnY08&feature=related. A map of the affected area can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/28yg. - Mod.PMB]
